<item>
            <title>[LU-1750] Update next_id even the previous process already clear the orphans</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1750</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;During orphan cleanup, OST should always update last_id, even though the previous threads might already cleanup orphans. Considering following case&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. mds start, send clear orphan req to OST, and OST begin to clear orphan, but then MDS fails before it gets reply. i.e. it does not update next_id yet.&lt;br/&gt;
2. mds restart and send clear orphan req again to OST with original next_id, then it found the orphan has been cleanup, so still reply with the original id, which is wrong, and we should update next_id in this case.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
